         <notesStmt>
            <note type="summary">1. Z. is slowly recuperating. 2. He does not know how
                            to respond regarding Rovigo's legal suit, because R. Leon Provinzal
                            swore to rent the house for three years. He suggests that Rovigo should
                            write a letter to bring the matter into as he sees fit by writing them a
                            letter to see how they will respond. 3. Z. praises his son-in-law's
                            desire to study Kabbalah. He does not know when he will return from
                            Venice in order to attend to this affairs and he fears that this delay
                            may be alaid out by the sitra aḥra. 4. Rovigo is not to heed the
                            teachings of R. Meir Rofe regarding the kavvanot. Z. lists evidence from
                            the Ari to this effect: the revelation of the Messiah, the return of the
                            Israelites to their ancestral lands.</note>
            <note type="incipit" xml:lang="he">גם כי הרחיב</note>
